<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFA76A18FCF292911B4BB3DE" pageId="92" pageNumber="850" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFA76A18FCF292911B4BB3DE" blockId="92.[781,1376,1149,1573]" lastBlockId="92.[169,1377,1580,3467]" pageId="92" pageNumber="850">
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA76A18FCF292911A10BFDB" baseAuthorityName="Tomes" baseAuthorityYear="1857" box="[782,1040,1224,1257]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="850" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pachyomus">Eptesicus pachyomus</taxonomicName>
was recently recognized as a distinct species from FE. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA76A18FB6592B61B06BE22" baseAuthorityName="Schreber" baseAuthorityYear="1774" box="[1177,1286,1263,1296]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="850" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="serotinus">serotinus</taxonomicName>
based on limited genetic and morphological data. In a recent genetic study by J. Juste and colleagues in 2013, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA76A18FB8C933F1B23BEB5" baseAuthorityName="Tomes" baseAuthorityYear="1857" box="[1136,1315,1382,1415]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="850" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pachyomus">E. pachyomus</taxonomicName>
was found to be either sister to 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA76A18FB7693D41B1CBE9C" baseAuthorityName="Schreber" baseAuthorityYear="1774" box="[1162,1308,1421,1454]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="850" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="serotinus">E. serotinus</taxonomicName>
with a high degree of separation (using nuclear genes) or sister to a clade including a paraphyletic 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA76A18FC7B905D1A1BBD17" baseAuthorityName="Schreber" baseAuthorityYear="1774" box="[903,1051,1540,1573]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="850" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="serotinus">E. serotinus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA76A18FBD7905D1AA2BD17" authorityName="Bobrinski" authorityYear="1918" box="[1067,1186,1540,1573]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="850" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ognevi">E. ognevi</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA76A18FB0E905D1B60BD17" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[1266,1376,1540,1573]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="850" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bottae">E. bottae</taxonomicName>
(using mitochondrial genes), butit consistently formed a monophyletic clade distinct from FE. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA76A18FEE3900A1F8DBD46" baseAuthorityName="Schreber" baseAuthorityYear="1774" box="[287,397,1619,1652]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="850" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="serotinus">serotinus</taxonomicName>
. Specific status of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA76A18FD68900A1D43BD46" baseAuthorityName="Tomes" baseAuthorityYear="1857" box="[660,835,1619,1652]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="850" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pachyomus">E. pachyomus</taxonomicName>
is still debatable because more recent genetic studies by I. V. Artyushin and colleagues in 2018 found conflicting results using mitochondrial and nuclear genes, with nuclear genes supporting the traditional view that 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA76A18FF1790931F80BDD9" baseAuthorityName="Schreber" baseAuthorityYear="1774" box="[235,384,1738,1771]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="850" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="serotinus">E. serotinus</taxonomicName>
includes both 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA76A18FDAA90931D00BDD9" box="[598,768,1738,1771]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="850" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="isabellinus">E. isabellinus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA76A18FCB790931DFBBDD9" baseAuthorityName="Tomes" baseAuthorityYear="1857" box="[843,1019,1738,1771]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="850" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pachyomus">E. pachyomus</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA76A18FBF090931B12BDD9" baseAuthorityName="Tomes" baseAuthorityYear="1857" box="[1036,1298,1738,1771]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="850" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pachyomus">Eptesicus pachyomus</taxonomicName>
is retained as a full species here, pending additional studies using rigorous genetic and morphological data across distributions of all taxa attributed to 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA76A18FC1291411A81BC0B" baseAuthorityName="Schreber" baseAuthorityYear="1774" box="[1006,1153,1816,1849]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="850" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" sensu="lato" species="serotinus">E. serotinus</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="EDD35797FFA76A18FB7691411B15BC0B" box="[1162,1301,1816,1849]" pageId="92" pageNumber="850" sensu="lato">sensu lato</taxonomicNameLabel>
. The Korean endemic taxon 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA76A18FE0691191CA3BC53" authorityName="Mori" authorityYear="1928" box="[506,675,1856,1889]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="850" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kobayashii">E. kobayashii</taxonomicName>
is typically recognized as distinct species, but this has been questioned because no recent records have been reported and there are very limited data to supportits specific status. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA76A18FD1C91D61DDBBC82" authorityName="Mori" authorityYear="1928" box="[736,987,1935,1968]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="850" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kobayashii">Eptesicus kobayashii</taxonomicName>
has variously been included under FE. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA76A18FED291EF1F97BCE5" baseAuthorityName="Keyserling &amp; Blasius" baseAuthorityYear="1839" box="[302,407,1974,2007]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="850" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nilssonii">nilssonii</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA76A18FE3991EF1C58BCE5" baseAuthorityName="Schreber" baseAuthorityYear="1774" box="[453,600,1974,2007]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="850" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="serotinus">E. serotinus</taxonomicName>
, but it appears to have more of an affinity to 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA76A18FB3291EF1B60BCE5" baseAuthorityName="Schreber" baseAuthorityYear="1774" box="[1230,1376,1974,2007]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="850" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="serotinus">E. serotinus</taxonomicName>
(now 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA76A18FF0691871FA6BCCD" baseAuthorityName="Tomes" baseAuthorityYear="1857" box="[250,422,2014,2047]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="850" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pachyomus">E. pachyomus</taxonomicName>
) and is tentatively included as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA76A18FBF091871AB8BCCD" baseAuthorityName="Tomes" baseAuthorityYear="1857" box="[1036,1208,2014,2047]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="850" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pachyomus">E. pachyomus</taxonomicName>
pallens until additional studies can prove its distinction. Taxon pashtonus is considered a synonym of the nominate subspecies here because it does not appear to be morphologically distinctive enough to represent a distinct subspecies. Exact distributional limits between 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA76A18FF569E221F56B3AE" baseAuthorityName="Tomes" baseAuthorityYear="1857" box="[170,342,2171,2204]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="850" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pachyomus">E. pachyomus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA76A18FE659E221C2AB3AE" baseAuthorityName="Schreber" baseAuthorityYear="1774" box="[409,554,2171,2204]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="850" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="serotinus">E. serotinus</taxonomicName>
are still uncertain in 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFFA76A18FCB19E221D88B3AE" box="[845,904,2171,2204]" name="Iran" pageId="92" pageNumber="850">Iran</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFFA76A18FC699E221A3FB3AE" box="[917,1087,2171,2204]" name="Afghanistan" pageId="92" pageNumber="850">Afghanistan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFFA76A18FBB29E221AC3B3AE" box="[1102,1219,2171,2204]" name="Pakistan" pageId="92" pageNumber="850">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFFA76A18FB2E9E221B1BB3AE" box="[1234,1307,2171,2204]" name="India" pageId="92" pageNumber="850">India</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFFA76A18FF579EFA1F00B3F6" box="[171,256,2211,2244]" name="China" pageId="92" pageNumber="850">China</collectingCountry>
. Distinctions among subspecies might be weak, and geographical boundaries between each are uncertain, requiring additional research. Four subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
